{{Infobox MMA event|name=Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship: Art of War 3|image=This_is_a_poster_for_the_MMA_event_Art_of_War_3.jpg|promotion=[[Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship]]|date=September 1, 2007|venue=[[American Airlines Center]]|city=[[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Texas]]|attendance=8,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmaweekly.com/rizzo-kos-the-snowman-at-art-of-war|title=– RIZZO DEFEATS MONSON ON "ART OF WAR" SHOW - MMAWeekly.com|website=www.mmaweekly.com}}</ref>|gate=|buyrate=|previousevent=[[Art of War 2]]|followingevent=[[Art of War 4]]}}

'''''Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship: Art of War 3''''' was the third [[mixed martial arts]] event by the mixed martial arts organization [[Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship]]. The event took place on Saturday, September 1, 2007<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/pressreleases/MonsonRizzo-Headline-Art-of-War-8695|title=Monson-Rizzo Headline Art of War|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref> at the [[American Airlines Center]] in [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://adcombat.com/news2007-05-16span-idlw11793298710-styleborder-bottom-1px-dashed-rgb0-102-204-height-1emusaspan-vs/|title=USA VS.  BRAZIL ON ART OF WAR 3 JUNE 30 IN |date=2007-05-15|work=ADCC NEWS|access-date=2018-02-21|language=en-US}}</ref>  The card aired on [[AXS TV]] formally HDNet. The television broadcast was produced by Allan Colton, [[Dustin Hodge]], and John Jones.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7466222/?ref_=ttfc_fc_tt</ref>

== History ==
The fight card included [[Pedro Rizzo]] and [[Jeff Monson]] in the main event.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lzdXP08P1pkC&pg=PT672&lpg=PT672&dq=art+of+war+3+rizzo+monson&source=bl&ots=CiPKCj6Uf6&sig=eNT0w8JeYWrway314TyNKxIHMLk&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0ocbk6bfZAhUQ2mMKHaD6DAsQ6AEIXTAM#v=onepage&q=art%20of%20war%203%20rizzo%20monson&f=false|title=The MMA Encyclopedia|last=Snowden|first=Jonathan|last2=Shields|first2=Kendall|date=November 2010|publisher=ECW Press|isbn=9781554908448|language=en}}</ref>  The show also featured a bout between [[Jorge Santiago]] and [[Jeremy Horn]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmatorch.com/artman2/publish/Other_News_4/article_693.shtml|title=UAFC News: Complete Art of War 3 - USA vs. Brazil Results with Jeff Monson vs. Pedro Rizzo|website=www.mmatorch.com|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref>

